Anton and Julia are going to get married, and they arrange evening meetings for their parents. Suddenly it turns out that Larissa, the mother of Anton, and Vladimir, the father of Julia, in their youth were familiar with each other. Moreover, that modest and inconspicuous Larisa then fell in love with secure and arrogant Vladimir has itself initiated their proximity.

Now Vladimir is a successful businessman having the care of beloved daughter Julia and his wife with a disability. The energetic and healthy man looks with interest at the lovely and charming Larisa who has suddenly emerged again in his life. Meeting with Vladimir stirs up old feminine feelings. Larissa can not cope with them and appeals for help to a psychologist, who calls it the status of "innuendo syndrome" and offers the only true way to get rid of it -- sex with the former lover ...
